cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.ST, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new Bayesian approach for Gaussian processes that learns basis dictionary elements and prior precisions in a sparse finite model. This approach is related to machine learning and statistical inference, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new learning method for Gaussian processes. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also likely categories as they often use Gaussian processes for modeling and prediction tasks. cs.ST (Statistics) is another possible category as the paper discusses statistical inference and model selection. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention neural networks or evolutionary algorithms, but it is still related to machine learning and optimization.
